### 1. REST Controllers
`@RestController` registers a class as a REST endpoint. It is a convenience annotation that combines `@Controller` and `@ResponseBody`, returning response data directly to the client as JSON:

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/users") // Base mapping URL path
public class UserController {

    @GetMapping // Maps HTTP GET requests
    public List<User> getUsers() { return userService.findAll(); }

    @PostMapping // Maps HTTP POST requests
    public User createUser(@RequestBody User user) {
        return userService.save(user);
    }
}
```

