### 2. Custom Validator Implementation
Create a custom annotation and implement `ConstraintValidator`:
```java
// 1. Define custom annotation
@Constraint(validatedBy = PhoneValidator.class)
@Target({ ElementType.FIELD })
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
public @interface ValidPhone {
    String message() default "Invalid phone number";
    Class<?>[] groups() default {};
    Class<? extends Payload>[] payload() default {};
}

// 2. Implement validator
public class PhoneValidator implements ConstraintValidator<ValidPhone, String> {
    public boolean isValid(String value, ConstraintValidatorContext context) {
        return value != null && value.matches("\\d{10}"); // Validates 10-digit number
    }
}
```

### 1. Why Centralized Configuration?
In microservice architectures with hundreds of instances, modifying configuration files (like database passwords) manually is impossible.

