### 2. Spring Cloud Config
Provides centralized server-side configuration management, storing configurations in a Git repository or database:
*   **Config Server**: Reads configuration files from a Git repository, serving them to microservices on startup.
*   **Config Client**: Microservices fetch their configurations from the Config Server on startup.
*   **@RefreshScope**: Reloads configurations dynamically at runtime without restarting the application:
    ```java
    @RestController
    @RefreshScope // Reloads variable values on /actuator/refresh calls
    public class FeatureController {
        @Value("${feature.toggle}")
        private boolean active;
    }
    ```
